overview: >-
  The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic appeal of
  their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The
  agent began by conducting a thorough review of the existing visual design,
  identifying areas such as the color palette, typography, spacing, form
  elements, and overall visual interest as needing improvement.

  The approach involved a multi-step redesign. First, a new sleep-themed color
  palette with deep indigos, purples, and calming teals was introduced in
  , along with custom utility classes for gradients and shadows.
  Subsequently, the main  layout was enhanced with decorative
  background elements, a redesigned progress indicator, and a subtle star
  pattern overlay on card headers. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and the progress bar received significant styling updates
  for a more polished and interactive feel.

  The  was transformed with a hero section and feature cards, and
  all 14 questionnaire sections were updated to use consistent, themed
  card-style groupings, replacing the previous plain gray boxes. The
   also received a major overhaul to unify its card headers and
  text colors with the new theme.

  During the process, a React console error concerning  values being
  passed to input components was identified and fixed by modifying the
  component to safely handle  values. User feedback, including a
  screenshot, was crucial in pinpointing and resolving remaining inconsistencies
  in the Report section's hardcoded colors. The outcome is a visually cohesive,
  calming, and professional sleep health application.
